{"about_the_game":"<img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2025810/extras/Non-Euclidean_small.gif?t=1686039247\" /><h2 class=\"bb_tag\">ABOUT</h2><br>Lavrynthos is <strong>an independently created VR short, a funny and philosophic story</strong> that places you at the heart of the labyrinth of Crete to tell you the story of the unlikely relationship between the Minotaur and his next meal: a girl named Cora. <br><br>In this experience, you'll get lost in a huge maze. You'll obviously want to find your way out, don't you ?  Well, actually... maybe you won't. <br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2025810/extras/CoraRun_Small.gif?t=1686039247\" /><br><br><strong>Dive into a contemporary Greek tragedy</strong> paying homage to modern dramatic theory while challenging it at the same time. Lavrynthos is a humorous take on a 3000 years old myth. Navigate an infinite non-euclidean maze that shifts space and time. What will you find?  Lavrynthos will distort your sense of direction, space and balance and you might even <strong> find yourself lost inside your own bedroom</strong>.<br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2025810/extras/Amphitheater.gif?t=1686039247\" /><br><br>Created with support of the Venice Biennale College, Lavrythos premiered at Venice Film Festival and in 2022 won the Stereopsia Crystal Owl <strong>Award for Best Creative Experience</strong>.<br><br><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2025810/extras/Leaves_Small.gif?t=1686039247\" />","background":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2025810/page_bg_generated_v6b.jpg?t=1686039247","background_raw":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2025810/page.bg.jpg?t=1686039247","capsule_image":"https://shared.akamai.s